	"title": "Angry Mom's Computer Nightmare",
	"content": "It was only a matter of time before I found myself in the uncomfortable position of having to apologize for something that could have easily been prevented. It all started when my daughter, Emily, asked me if she could use her computer. She had just gotten her driver's license and wanted to learn how to navigate it herself. Without hesitation, I allowed her to go online and start browsing through Google. At first, everything was fine. She navigated the web with ease, even typing in a password or two. But as she started searching for something specific, my heart sank. The results were terrifying."
