temp_1.0_output:
{
    "title": "Budget Denial: The Corrupt Reason",
    "content": "It's a familiar sight: a large, shiny, bumper sticker on the windshield of your company car advertising ‘Budget Denied’. A simple catchphrase that you know will resonate with everyone who has ever rolled their eyes at a corporate budget plan or committee meeting. It's not an entirely useless soundbite—many executives have gotten away with denying budgets in the past, knowing full well that if they had to face up to the reality of cutting corners and layoffs, they might be out a job. The issue isn't so much that you didn't take it seriously (or that others didn’t either), but rather how you present the situation. You need to be very convincing about the reason for the budget denial—in other words, what exactly the company is doing wrong in order to justify a cut."
    ,"word_count":521,"style_elements":["bold","italic","underline","strikethrough","link","ol","ul","quote","code","heading","paragraph"]}

